<section class="gbd-tool" id="pollinator-fit-tool">
  <section class="card">
    <span class="gbd-kicker">Free climate-fit plant matrix</span>
    <p class="lede">
      Filter pollinator plants by cold hardiness, sun, moisture, height, bloom season, deer pressure, and garden goal. Use it to build a climate-aware shortlist before you shop at a nursery or build a planting plan.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      This is a selection matrix, not a custom landscape design. Regional native status varies, so verify local nativity and invasive status with your extension office, native plant society, or provincial/state resources before planting.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card" aria-labelledby="pft-filters-title">
    <h2 id="pft-filters-title">1. Filter your site conditions</h2>
    <div class="gbd-grid three">
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-zone">Hardiness zone</label>
        <select id="pft-zone">
          <option value="2">Zone 2</option>
          <option value="3">Zone 3</option>
          <option value="4" selected>Zone 4</option>
          <option value="5">Zone 5</option>
          <option value="6">Zone 6</option>
          <option value="7">Zone 7</option>
          <option value="8">Zone 8</option>
          <option value="9">Zone 9</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-sun">Sun exposure</label>
        <select id="pft-sun">
          <option value="any">Any</option>
          <option value="full" selected>Full sun</option>
          <option value="part">Part sun</option>
          <option value="shade">Shade / part shade</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-moisture">Soil moisture</label>
        <select id="pft-moisture">
          <option value="any">Any</option>
          <option value="dry" selected>Dry / drought-prone</option>
          <option value="average">Average</option>
          <option value="moist">Moist / rain garden</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gbd-grid three" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-height">Maximum mature height</label>
        <select id="pft-height">
          <option value="999">Any height</option>
          <option value="18">Under 18 in.</option>
          <option value="36" selected>Under 3 ft.</option>
          <option value="60">Under 5 ft.</option>
          <option value="96">Under 8 ft.</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-bloom">Bloom season needed</label>
        <select id="pft-bloom">
          <option value="any">Any</option>
          <option value="spring">Spring</option>
          <option value="early-summer">Early summer</option>
          <option value="summer" selected>Summer</option>
          <option value="late-summer">Late summer</option>
          <option value="fall">Fall</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-goal">Primary goal</label>
        <select id="pft-goal">
          <option value="any">Any pollinator value</option>
          <option value="bees" selected>Bees</option>
          <option value="butterflies">Butterflies</option>
          <option value="hummingbirds">Hummingbirds</option>
          <option value="monarchs">Monarch support</option>
          <option value="front-yard">Front-yard friendly</option>
          <option value="rain-garden">Rain garden</option>
          <option value="drought">Drought-tolerant planting</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gbd-grid three" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-deer">Deer pressure</label>
        <select id="pft-deer">
          <option value="any" selected>Any</option>
          <option value="prefer-resistant">Prefer deer-resistant options</option>
          <option value="strict-resistant">Only stronger deer-resistance candidates</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-type">Plant type</label>
        <select id="pft-type">
          <option value="any" selected>Any type</option>
          <option value="perennial">Perennial</option>
          <option value="grass">Grass / sedge</option>
          <option value="shrub">Shrub</option>
          <option value="annual">Annual / self-seeding</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-field">
        <label for="pft-strict">Match strictness</label>
        <select id="pft-strict">
          <option value="ranked" selected>Ranked matches, include near-fits</option>
          <option value="strict">Strict matches only</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gbd-actions" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <button class="gbd-button primary" type="button" id="pft-filter">Find plants</button>
      <button class="gbd-button" type="button" id="pft-reset">Reset filters</button>
      <button class="gbd-button" type="button" id="pft-csv">Download shortlist CSV</button>
      <button class="gbd-button" type="button" onclick="window.print()">Print</button>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card" id="pft-results-card" data-gbd-results tabindex="-1" aria-live="polite" aria-labelledby="pft-results-title">
    <h2 id="pft-results-title">2. Climate-fit shortlist</h2>
    <div class="gbd-kpis" id="pft-kpis" style="margin-top:.75rem;"></div>
    <div class="gbd-grid two" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div class="gbd-panel soft">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0;">Bloom coverage</h3>
        <div class="gbd-bars" id="pft-bloom-bars"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="gbd-panel soft">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0;">Shopping strategy</h3>
        <ul class="gbd-summary-list" id="pft-strategy"></ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="gbd-table-wrap" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <table aria-label="Climate-fit pollinator plant finder results">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Plant</th>
            <th>Fit</th>
            <th>Zones</th>
            <th>Sun</th>
            <th>Moisture</th>
            <th>Height</th>
            <th>Bloom</th>
            <th>Best for</th>
            <th>Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody id="pft-results"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>How to use this plant matrix</h2>
    <p>
      Build a resilient pollinator planting by combining climate fit with season-long bloom. A good shortlist usually includes spring, summer, late-summer, and fall bloomers plus a few grasses or structural plants for habitat and winter interest.
    </p>
    <ul class="tight">
      <li><strong>Cold climates:</strong> prioritize zone margin. A Zone 4 garden is safer with Zone 3–4 hardy plants than plants barely listed to Zone 4.</li>
      <li><strong>Dry front yards:</strong> choose shorter drought-tolerant plants that look intentional, not just ecologically useful.</li>
      <li><strong>Rain gardens:</strong> filter for moist-soil plants, then check mature height before placing them near walkways.</li>
      <li><strong>Monarch support:</strong> include milkweeds plus nectar plants that bloom before and after milkweed flowering.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Important native plant caveat</h2>
    <p>
      “Native” is local. A plant can be native to parts of North America but not to your county, province, state, or ecoregion. This tool is a climate and site-condition filter, not a definitive native-range authority. Use it to create a shortlist, then verify local suitability before buying.
    </p>
  </section>

